<br>
As far as skills go, I don't know.  A certain level of skill and intelligence is needed I suppose, but it is more like common sense.  Where to hunt based on our Verant given abilities, toggeling between your target and yourself to cast Celestial Cleansing, root-parking, knowing when to stop and med, knowing your escape routes, etc.  A lot of this, however, you should know, or be able to do simply instinctivly, so I find it hard to say one has &quot;733t 5kiLL2(tm)&quot; because they can root a mob and helm heal themselves.<br>
<br>
Put a Palladius axe in the hands of a lvl 55 paladin using a Arbitors sword, and his soloing abilities will shoot up a lot theoretically.  Does that mean he can't do it without it?  Some people get themselves into this mental rut thinking that's the truth because they see someone uber who has great gear solo effectivly, but that doesn't mean we can't.  <br>
<br>
All I am getting at is gear makes it easier, sometimes to the point of it being mindless, but it doesn't dictate wether we can or can't do it.  Unless of course you have a rusty axe and cloth pants, then you'd just be so uber you'd get banned anyways :) <p><font face="arial" size="-1"><a href=mailto:mirithal@hotmail.com>Mirithal Darkbuster 59 Paladin  <b>||</b>  Maepole 43 Warrior</a><br>
